<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-243-502  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 243 502.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  March 13 1990 v4 n10 p18(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SAS Institute offers net version of JMP. (JMP Serve, a networkstatistical visualization package) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Norr, Henry.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   SAS Institute Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   JMP Serve (Statistical software) (product introduction)Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSoftware PackagesStatisticsVisualization.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Henry NorrandM;Cary, N.C.andP;  -- SAS Institute Inc. last week announced JMP Serve, a networkversion of the JMP statistical visualization package for the Macintosh.andM;The new version promises a convenient and economical way for corporate anduniversity sites to accommodate a large number of JMP users without runningthe risk of exceeding their software licenses.andP;  JMP Serve polls AppleTalk totrack the number of copies of the program concurrently in use; when thenumber licensed is reached, further launches from any network node areprevented and a list of current users is displayed, the Institute said.andM;The network version adds no new statistical or graphical capabilities to JMP,a package that combines classical statistics with interactive graphics.andM;JMP Serve is available to corporate customers in a variety of packages,including a five pack for $2,500 per user and packages for 20 or more userspriced at $400 per user.andP;  For degree-granting institutions, prices range from$900 for a five pack to $100 per user for licenses with 30 or more copies.andO;Pricing includes one set of manuals and a year of free technical support.andM;List price of the single-user JMP package is $695.andP;  A minimum of 2 Mbytes ofmemory is recommended.andM;SAS Institute Inc. is at SAS Circle, Box 8000, Cary, N.C.andP;  27512-8000; (919)467-8000.andP;  n</TEXT></DOC>